<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1131" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1131">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4514.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                                    Juárez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juárez</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mexican consul at El Paso, who is in Chargé of Federal troops north of
                            Casas Grandes, promises to give immediate orders to crowd rebels in that
                            section. I would suggest curtailment of importations at this port to the
                            United States, as well as exports. Rebels are gathering funds from
                            collections on imports and exports, which induces them to remain;
                            curtailment would weaken them and hasten their departure. Great alarm
                            caused by statements of subordinate rebel officers of intention to force
                            intervention. Conditions will improve with Federal advance.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>